01:09:48,584 --> 01:09:52,076
<i>Well, I have to tell you, Steve,
he's within his rights.</i>

1066
01:09:52,121 --> 01:09:55,056
<i>The things you did
were fireable offenses.</i>

1067
01:09:55,090 --> 01:09:58,526
<i>I know, I'm not saying
that they weren't.</i>

1068
01:09:59,528 --> 01:10:03,396
<i>I did some terrible,
terrible things.</i>

1069
01:10:06,969 --> 01:10:09,802
<i>But believe me, Michael,
Chuck doesn't care about any of it.</i>

1070
01:10:10,839 --> 01:10:14,104
<i>It's my loyalty to you
that he's punishing me for.</i>

1071
01:10:14,143 --> 01:10:17,601
<i>I'm such an idiot.</i>

1072
01:10:17,646 --> 01:10:19,978
<i>Now who's going to hire me?</i>

1073
01:10:21,684 --> 01:10:25,120
Steve, I have to ask you
something.

1074
01:10:27,523 --> 01:10:30,117
<i>Did you ever "cook" a piece
when I was your boss?</i>

1075
01:10:32,661 --> 01:10:35,061
<i>Did you ever lie to me?</i>

1076
01:10:36,732 --> 01:10:39,792
<i>The "Young Conservatives" piece,
the mini-bottles?</i>

1077
01:10:39,835 --> 01:10:42,395
<i>Was that true?</i>

1078
01:11:00,889 --> 01:11:03,653
- Hello.
- Chuck, it's David Bach.

1079
01:11:03,692 --> 01:11:06,058
<i>I'm really sorry to bother you at night,
but it seemed important.</i>

1080
01:11:07,062 --> 01:11:09,053
<i>It's fine.
Is there a problem?</i>

1081
01:11:09,098 --> 01:11:11,566
<i>Well, I don't know.</i>

1082
01:11:11,600 --> 01:11:13,693
I just got off the phone
with Stephen.

1083
01:11:13,736 --> 01:11:15,931
<i>He sounds horrible.</i>

1084
01:11:15,971 --> 01:11:17,996
Did you suspend him,
Chuck?

1085
01:11:18,040 --> 01:11:21,066
<i>David,
what is the problem?</i>

1086
01:11:21,110 --> 01:11:24,978
<i>He asked me if I would drive him
out to Dulles later tonight.</i>

1087
01:11:25,014 --> 01:11:27,574
<i>He said he wasn't sure
he'd be safe driving by himself.</i>

1088
01:11:27,616 --> 01:11:30,244
<i>I just thought I should
draw your attention to that.</i>

1089
01:11:30,286 --> 01:11:32,345
<i>Did he say
where he was going?</i>

1090
01:11:32,388 --> 01:11:35,152
<i>Yeah, he said he'd be staying
with his family for a while.</i>

1091
01:11:35,190 --> 01:11:37,021
<i>That could only be
one of two places.</i>

1092
01:11:37,059 --> 01:11:39,050
<i>His parents live
in Highland Park, right?</i>

1093
01:11:39,094 --> 01:11:42,825
<i>Yeah. Or his brother,
out in Palo Alto.</i>

1094
01:11:42,865 --> 01:11:45,993
<i>- I'm sorry?
- His brother, at Stanford.</i>

1095
01:11:46,035 --> 01:11:48,663
<i>Chuck?</i>

1096
01:12:06,488 --> 01:12:08,581
<i>You had your brother pose
as "George Sims."</i>

1097
01:12:08,624 --> 01:12:10,319
What?

1098
01:12:10,359 --> 01:12:12,793
<i>The phony recording
from Jukt Micronics?</i>

1099
01:12:12,828 --> 01:12:15,262
<i>It's a Palo Alto number.</i>

1100
01:12:15,297 --> 01:12:18,494
<i>Your brother is a student at Stanford.
You had him pose as Sims.</i>

1101
01:12:18,534 --> 01:12:20,729
<i>- No, Sims is a real guy...
- Steve, Steve...</i>

1102
01:12:20,769 --> 01:12:23,431
<i>I've talked to him a million times.
My brother and I aren't speaking...</i>

1103
01:12:23,472 --> 01:12:26,600
Stop it. You faked Sims,
you faked a website...

1104
01:12:26,642 --> 01:12:28,906
<i>- You faked all those voicemails...
- You don't know, Chuck.</i>

1105
01:12:28,944 --> 01:12:31,504
<i>- Restil, Hiert, Ghort...
- You got this totally backward.</i>

1106
01:12:31,547 --> 01:12:35,074
<i>It's all crap. I can trace it if you
make me. I'll find it all billed to you.</i>

1107
01:12:35,117 --> 01:12:37,745
<i>I don't know what you're talking about.
Those are all real people.</i>

1108
01:12:37,786 --> 01:12:40,482
<i>- They are?
- Yeah.</i>

1109
01:12:41,590 --> 01:12:44,388
Look at me.

1110
01:12:44,426 --> 01:12:46,724
And say that again.

1111
01:12:46,762 --> 01:12:50,254
<i>Those are all real people.</i>

1112
01:12:53,802 --> 01:12:56,737
Tsk... okay.

1113
01:12:58,574 --> 01:13:00,701
<i>I want you out of here.</i>

1114
01:13:00,743 --> 01:13:02,210
What?

1115
01:13:02,244 --> 01:13:04,371
<i>I want you out of here,</i>

1116
01:13:04,413 --> 01:13:06,745
<i>and you can't take anything
with you.</i>

1117
01:13:06,782 --> 01:13:10,718
<i>There are some files, okay?
I have to put them on a disk.</i>

1118
01:13:10,753 --> 01:13:13,119
<i>- No.
- No, there are mine. Personal stuff!</i>

1119
01:13:13,155 --> 01:13:15,316
<i>I don't care.</i>

1120
01:13:17,259 --> 01:13:19,750
I know you don't.

1121
01:13:20,963 --> 01:13:23,193
<i>- Can I at least shut down my computer?
- Don't touch it!</i>

1122
01:13:23,232 --> 01:13:25,723
<i>- I'm in the middle of a file, Chuck!
- Back away from the desk!</i>

1123
01:13:25,768 --> 01:13:27,861
<i>- God damn it!
- Leave it or I will call Security!</i>

1124
01:13:27,903 --> 01:13:30,269
<i>- Jesus Christ.
- Okay?</i>

1125
01:13:34,343 --> 01:13:36,470
Can I take my Rolodex?

1126
01:13:37,513 --> 01:13:39,640
Steve...

1127
01:13:42,284 --> 01:13:44,275
Can I take my law books?

1128
01:13:44,319 --> 01:13:46,446
<i>Sure.</i>

1129
01:13:49,558 --> 01:13:52,584
<i>But I'm gonna need to have
your security key.</i>

1130
01:13:55,230 --> 01:13:58,825
<i>I'm not a criminal, Chuck.</i>

1131
01:14:00,302 --> 01:14:02,532
<i>Okay?</i>

1132
01:14:05,174 --> 01:14:08,871
<i>- I'm not a criminal.
- Oh, I heard you.</i>

1133
01:14:08,911 --> 01:14:11,243
Come on.

1134
01:14:31,667 --> 01:14:34,067
Chuck...?

1135
01:14:44,413 --> 01:14:46,745
<i>I said I was sorry.</i>

1136
01:14:46,782 --> 01:14:49,273
I know.

1137
01:14:49,318 --> 01:14:52,219
But you have to go.

1138
01:15:53,715 --> 01:15:55,876
<i>"Bond traders as a rule,</i>

1139
01:15:55,918 --> 01:15:57,909
<i>do not have much time
to loaf around.</i>

1140
01:15:57,953 --> 01:16:00,217
<i>And the Wall Street
investment house, RVL,</i>

1141
01:16:00,255 --> 01:16:02,917
<i>takes its work ethic
to a particularly..."</i>

1142
01:16:02,958 --> 01:16:06,257
<i>"...one trader is now testing
a hand-held urinal</i>

1143
01:16:06,295 --> 01:16:08,627
<i>normally used
by cops on stakeouts..."</i>

1144
01:16:10,098 --> 01:16:12,498
<i>"A few days after Mike Tyson
was disqualified</i>

1145
01:16:12,534 --> 01:16:14,661
<i>for biting Evander Holyfield,</i>

1146
01:16:14,703 --> 01:16:17,331
<i>I offered half a dozen talk shows
my services as a biting expert.</i>

1147
01:16:17,372 --> 01:16:19,397
<i>I'm someone who knows..."</i>

1148
01:16:19,441 --> 01:16:22,433
<i>"The mini-bar is open,
and empty little bottles of booze</i>

1149
01:16:22,477 --> 01:16:24,672
<i>are scattered on the carpet. "</i>

1150
01:16:24,713 --> 01:16:26,442
<i>"It was the monthly gathering</i>

1151
01:16:26,481 --> 01:16:29,678
<i>of 'The Commission to Restore
the Presidency to Greatness. "'</i>

1152
01:16:29,718 --> 01:16:31,948
<i>"Patriotic prophets
will have a hard time</i>

1153
01:16:31,987 --> 01:16:34,455
<i>holding back
this merchandising bonanza..."</i>

1154
01:16:53,809 --> 01:16:56,744
<i>- Thanks, George, sorry for the trouble.
- No problem, Steve.</i>

1155
01:17:11,593 --> 01:17:13,720
Chuck?

1156
01:17:16,698 --> 01:17:19,098
Um...

1157
01:17:20,168 --> 01:17:22,966
<i>The... the thing
with George Sims?</i>

1158
01:17:24,039 --> 01:17:26,166
<i>That was...</i>

1159
01:17:26,208 --> 01:17:28,699
<i>the voice... the voice that you heard
on the telephone,</i>

1160
01:17:29,745 --> 01:17:32,737
<i>that was my brother.
I'm sorry.</i>

1161
01:17:37,352 --> 01:17:39,786
<i>There really is a George Sims.</i>

1162
01:17:39,821 --> 01:17:41,846
<i>L... I've spoken to him
a million times.</i>

1163
01:17:41,890 --> 01:17:44,358
He just stopped talking to me.

1164
01:17:44,393 --> 01:17:46,725
<i>You know,
because of the article.</i>

1165
01:17:46,762 --> 01:17:50,858
He was so mad about it.
I didn't know what to do.

1166
01:17:50,899 --> 01:17:53,663
<i>And the guys from Forbes were
putting so much pressure on me.</i>

1167
01:17:53,702 --> 01:17:55,897
<i>You know?
And you were so mad!</i>

1168
01:17:55,937 --> 01:17:59,998
<i>I just thought that if I could get
everybody off my back, okay?</i>

1169
01:18:00,042 --> 01:18:02,135
<i>For just a day.</i>

1170
01:18:02,177 --> 01:18:04,702
Just a day would give me
enough time to... go and find him.

1171
01:18:04,746 --> 01:18:07,112
<i>You can understand that,
can't you?</i>

1172
01:18:08,116 --> 01:18:10,141
<i>You're fired, Steve.</i>

1173
01:18:10,185 --> 01:18:12,745
What?

1174
01:18:14,122 --> 01:18:17,091
<i>You're fired.
You've lost your job.</i>

1175
01:18:20,996 --> 01:18:23,556
But you can't...

1176
01:18:48,957 --> 01:18:51,016
Chuck...

1177
01:18:51,059 --> 01:18:53,653
<i>will you please
take me to the airport?</i>

1178
01:18:54,663 --> 01:18:57,154
<i>Jesus.</i>

1179
01:18:57,199 --> 01:18:59,565
Please, okay?

1180
01:18:59,601 --> 01:19:02,297
You don't have to talk to me
if you don't want to.

1181
01:19:02,337 --> 01:19:05,795
It's fine.

1182
01:19:05,841 --> 01:19:08,469
<i>But I can't be by myself
right now.</i>

1183
01:19:09,911 --> 01:19:12,471
Okay? I'm...

1184
01:19:12,514 --> 01:19:16,177
<i>I'm afraid
of what I'm going to do.</i>

1185
01:19:16,218 --> 01:19:19,745
<i>And you know,
I... I can't get there by myself.</i>

1186
01:19:21,757 --> 01:19:24,351
<i>I'm not going anywhere
with you.</i>

1187
01:19:25,360 --> 01:19:27,624
<i>Now, if you feel like
you're a danger to yourself,</i>

1188
01:19:27,662 --> 01:19:30,688
<i>you can sit down for a few minutes
until you feel calm enough to go.</i>

1189
01:19:30,732 --> 01:19:32,927
<i>But I am not going anywhere
with you.</i>

1190
01:19:32,968 --> 01:19:36,404
<i>But... I'm afraid that I'm...</i>

1191
01:19:36,438 --> 01:19:38,906
I'm going to do something,
okay?

1192
01:19:40,208 --> 01:19:42,369
<i>Did you hear what I said?</i>

1193
01:19:42,410 --> 01:19:44,776
Yeah.

1194
01:19:46,314 --> 01:19:49,010
<i>It's a hell of a story.</i>

1195
01:19:51,820 --> 01:19:54,084
Chuck, please?

1196
01:19:55,657 --> 01:19:59,354
<i>Stop pitching, Steve.
It's over.</i>

1197
01:20:33,061 --> 01:20:36,963
<i>"Spring Breakdown,"
"The Jungle."</i>

1198
01:20:36,998 --> 01:20:40,661
<i>"A Fine Mess,"
"After the Fall,"</i>

1199
01:20:40,702 --> 01:20:45,071
"Peddling Poppy,"
"Cheap Suits,"

1200
01:20:45,106 --> 01:20:49,202
<i>"Kicked Out,"
"No Free Launch,"</i>

1201
01:20:49,244 --> 01:20:51,678
<i>"Ratted Out,"
"State of Nature,"</i>

1202
01:20:51,713 --> 01:20:55,581
<i>"Clutch Situation,"
"All Wet," "Plotters,"</i>

1203
01:20:55,617 --> 01:20:59,986
<i>"Praised Be Greenspan,"
"Monica Sells..."</i>

1204
01:21:00,922 --> 01:21:03,413
"Hack Heaven."

1205
01:21:10,298 --> 01:21:12,698
What the hell did you do
to Steve?!

1206
01:21:12,734 --> 01:21:15,134
<i>He called me from his car, hysterical.
I asked him what was wrong,</i>

1207
01:21:15,170 --> 01:21:18,230
<i>- he said, "Ask Chuck..."
- I fired him, okay?!</i>

1208
01:21:24,145 --> 01:21:26,636
<i>Not suspended, fired.</i>

1209
01:21:26,681 --> 01:21:30,173
Because this wasn't
an isolated incident, Caitlin.

1210
01:21:30,218 --> 01:21:32,049
<i>He cooked a dozen
of them, maybe more.</i>

1211
01:21:32,087 --> 01:21:35,284
<i>We're going to have to go
through them, you and I. All of them.</i>

1212
01:21:35,323 --> 01:21:38,053
No, the only one was "Hack Heaven."
He told me that himself!

1213
01:21:38,093 --> 01:21:41,221
<i>If he were a stranger to you, if he was
a guy you were doing a piece about,</i>

1214
01:21:41,263 --> 01:21:43,754
<i>pretend that guy told you
he'd "only done it once."</i>

1215
01:21:43,798 --> 01:21:46,028
<i>Would you take his word for it?</i>

1216
01:21:46,067 --> 01:21:48,126
<i>Of course not,
you'd dig and you'd bury him!</i>

1217
01:21:48,169 --> 01:21:50,262
And you'd be offended
if anybody told you not to.

1218
01:21:50,305 --> 01:21:52,569
<i>Everyone of those pieces
was fact-checked. They...</i>

1219
01:21:52,607 --> 01:21:55,371
So was "Hack Heaven"!

1220
01:21:58,013 --> 01:22:00,140
<i>You're a good reporter.</i>

1221
01:22:00,181 --> 01:22:04,345
<i>You've always been a smart, thorough
reporter. Why can't you be one now?</i>

1222
01:22:04,386 --> 01:22:07,082
<i>Because what you're telling me
is impossible, Chuck.</i>

1223
01:22:07,122 --> 01:22:09,317
<i>Go upstairs.</i>

1224
01:22:09,357 --> 01:22:12,952
- Read them again.
- This is bullshit!

1225
01:22:12,994 --> 01:22:14,985
<i>Make sure you go
all the way back,</i>

1226
01:22:15,030 --> 01:22:18,625
<i>because half of them ran
when Mike was still here.</i>

1227
01:22:19,634 --> 01:22:22,000
<i>That's what this is.
Of course.</i>

1228
01:22:22,037 --> 01:22:25,666
<i>What are you going to do, Chuck,
pick us off, one by one?</i>

1229
01:22:25,707 --> 01:22:28,403
<i>Everybody that was loyal to Mike,
so you have a staff that belongs to you?</i>

1230
01:22:28,443 --> 01:22:30,638
<i>Is that the kind of magazine
you want to run?</i>

1231
01:22:30,679 --> 01:22:34,012
<i>When this thing blows, there isn't
going to be a magazine anymore.</i>

1232
01:22:34,049 --> 01:22:36,176
If you want to make this about Mike,
make it about Mike.

1233
01:22:36,217 --> 01:22:38,344
<i>I don't give a shit.
You can resent me,</i>

1234
01:22:38,386 --> 01:22:40,616
<i>you can hate me,
but come Monday morning,</i>

1235
01:22:40,655 --> 01:22:42,919
<i>we're all going to have to answer
for what we let happen here.</i>

1236
01:22:42,958 --> 01:22:45,859
<i>We're all going to have
an apology to make!</i>

1237
01:22:45,894 --> 01:22:49,159
<i>Jesus Christ! Don't you have any idea
how much shit we're about to eat?</i>

1238
01:22:49,197 --> 01:22:51,927
<i>Every competitor we ever took a shot at,
they're going to pounce.</i>

1239
01:22:51,967 --> 01:22:55,801
<i>And they should.
Because we blew it, Caitlin.</i>

1240
01:22:55,837 --> 01:22:58,135
<i>He handed us fiction after fiction</i>

1241
01:22:58,173 --> 01:23:00,641
<i>and we printed them all as fact.</i>

1242
01:23:01,643 --> 01:23:05,670
<i>Just because...
we found him "entertaining."</i>

1243
01:23:08,984 --> 01:23:11,077
It's indefensible.

1244
01:23:11,119 --> 01:23:13,952
Don't you know that?

1245
01:23:51,826 --> 01:23:55,125
<i>- Is everyone in the conference room?
- Um-hm.</i>

1246
01:23:58,033 --> 01:24:00,263
<i>You know what could've prevented
all this, don't you?</i>

1247
01:24:00,301 --> 01:24:02,235
No. What?

1248
01:24:02,270 --> 01:24:05,296
<i>Pictures.</i>

1249
01:24:06,307 --> 01:24:08,502
<i>How could you
make up characters</i>

1250
01:24:08,543 --> 01:24:11,444
<i>if everyone you wrote about
had to be photographed?</i>

1251
01:24:18,753 --> 01:24:20,880
<i>You know, Stephen...</i>

1252
01:24:20,922 --> 01:24:23,982
<i>if you wanted to, you could
do these kids a giant favor.</i>

1253
01:24:24,025 --> 01:24:26,323
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

1254
01:24:29,998 --> 01:24:32,967
<i>You could write something boring
one of these days.</i>

1255
01:24:33,001 --> 01:24:36,095
<i>Give them a little less
to live up to.</i>

1256
01:24:37,539 --> 01:24:39,666
I suppose I could.

1257
01:24:39,707 --> 01:24:43,438
<i>We don't want a bunch
of teenagers getting ulcers, do we?</i>

1258
01:24:46,881 --> 01:24:49,349
<i>Good morning.</i>

1259
01:24:50,885 --> 01:24:53,080
Hi.

1260
01:25:10,305 --> 01:25:12,705
It's funny...

1261
01:25:18,813 --> 01:25:21,907
...because I thought I was going
to have to explain all this to you.

1262
01:25:25,420 --> 01:25:29,413
Well, what do you think
of this guy?

1263
01:25:43,605 --> 01:25:45,664
Thank you.

1264
01:25:50,044 --> 01:25:52,171
Thank you.

1265
01:25:52,213 --> 01:25:54,477
<i>Thank you, everybody.</i>

1266
01:26:00,655 --> 01:26:03,453
Thanks.
Thank you.

1267
01:26:28,950 --> 01:26:31,214
<i>Steve?</i>

1268
01:26:32,253 --> 01:26:33,379
<i>Stephen?</i>

1269
01:26:36,024 --> 01:26:38,549
<i>We've read through
all the pieces now,</i>

1270
01:26:38,593 --> 01:26:41,926
<i>the entire staff, and we've
come up with a list of those</i>

1271
01:26:41,963 --> 01:26:45,296
<i>whose facts and sources
we couldn't verify independently.</i>

1272
01:26:46,401 --> 01:26:49,336
<i>I know you can't admit
guilt of any kind,</i>

1273
01:26:49,370 --> 01:26:52,100
<i>but I want you to confirm
a few titles for me.</i>

1274
01:26:52,140 --> 01:26:54,506
<i>We're not prepared
to confirm or deny anything...</i>

1275
01:26:54,542 --> 01:26:57,102
What I'm going to do is this.

1276
01:26:57,145 --> 01:27:00,706
<i>I'm going to read to you a list
of suspicious titles, one by one.</i>

1277
01:27:01,983 --> 01:27:04,543
<i>If you raise an objection
to a particular title,</i>

1278
01:27:04,586 --> 01:27:08,317
<i>we'll fact-check it again in the hope
of removing it from the list.</i>

1279
01:27:08,356 --> 01:27:12,816
<i>If you remain silent,
we'll assume that piece is fabricated...</i>

1280
01:27:12,860 --> 01:27:17,763
<i>either partially or entirely,
and it will stay on.</i>

1281
01:27:17,799 --> 01:27:20,632
<i>Is that clear to everyone?</i>

1282
01:27:23,371 --> 01:27:25,498
Okay.

1283
01:27:26,674 --> 01:27:28,665
<i>"Hazardous
To Your Mental Health."</i>

1284
01:27:33,514 --> 01:27:35,982
That means it stays
on the list of suspicious pieces.

1285
01:27:36,017 --> 01:27:38,178
<i>Fabricated pieces.</i>

1286
01:27:38,219 --> 01:27:41,655
<i>We understand.
Can we move along?</i>

1287
01:27:43,825 --> 01:27:46,350
<i>"Holy Trinity."</i>

1288
01:27:53,901 --> 01:27:56,870
<i>"Probable Claus"?</i>

1289
01:28:02,977 --> 01:28:05,309
<i>"Don't You Dare."</i>

1290
01:28:07,815 --> 01:28:10,283
<i>"Spring Breakdown."</i>

1291
01:28:12,854 --> 01:28:14,845
<i>"State Of Nature."</i>

1292
01:28:19,294 --> 01:28:22,024
<i>"Rock The Morons."</i>

1293
01:28:24,032 --> 01:28:26,398
<i>"After The Fall..."</i>

1294
01:28:26,434 --> 01:28:28,664
<i>You have to know
who you're writing for,</i>

1295
01:28:28,703 --> 01:28:31,035
<i>and you have to know
what you're good at.</i>

1296
01:28:31,072 --> 01:28:33,404
<i>I record what people do.</i>

1297
01:28:33,441 --> 01:28:36,103
<i>I find out what moves them,
what scares them,</i>

1298
01:28:36,144 --> 01:28:37,941
<i>and I write that down.</i>

1299
01:28:37,979 --> 01:28:40,504
<i>That way they're the ones
telling the story.</i>

1300
01:28:40,548 --> 01:28:42,573
<i>And you know what?</i>

1301
01:28:42,617 --> 01:28:45,085
<i>Those kinds of pieces
can win Pulitzers too.</i>

1302
01:28:46,087 --> 01:28:48,248
<i>Steve?</i>


